### Data Quality Check

The dataset was validated to ensure it was suitable for analysis. 
Data quality checks confirmed that the dataset is complete, with no missing values in the key fields used throughout the project. 
Additional validation found no duplicate records or invalid mortality values, indicating that the data is consistent and reliable.
These checks provide confidence that the subsequent Excel, SQL, R, and Power BI analyses are based on clean, high-quality data.

